{
  "text": "Several observations of traffic flow result in underlining two different behaviors, sometimes called phases, see [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . At low density and high speed, the flow appears to be reasonably described by a function of the (mean) traffic density. On the contrary, at high density and low speed, flow is not a single valued function of the density. This paper presents a model providing an explanation to this phenomenon, its two key features being:",
